I believe the best answer is that if software wants to have a special
case kludge then it should be the established one, i.e., numeric IP
addresses should look like [192.11.2.1].  I recommend that 3com.COM
be allowed to stay, and the non-numeric first-letter restriction be
removed.  (I hope this doesn't get abused.  I don't think 3COM is abusing it.)

Liudvikas Bukys
bukys@cs.rochester.edu

